## 5. Create .gitignore

Create `.gitignore` file:
```
# Environment variables (NEVER commit this!)
.env

# Python
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python

# Screenshots and output
*.png
*.html

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```

## 6. Project Structure

Your folder should look like this:
```
athenaeum-booking\
├── .env                      # Your secrets (NOT in git)
├── .env.example              # Template (safe for git)
├── .gitignore               # Protect secrets
├── athenaeum_booking.py     # Main script
├── venv\                    # Virtual environment
└── requirements.txt         # Dependencies (create this next)